						               													<description>90 min is a realistic football (soccer) simulation board game, designed not only for football fans.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Taking turns, the players move their pawns across the field in order to score a goal. Every turn represents 1 (advanced) or 2 (standard) min in the match. The players use a minutes track to monitor the progress of the match and after 90 min the game is over.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Different types of players and the fan support will influence the odds. Tackling, free kick, corner kick, throw-in and offside: 90 min implements almost every aspect of a real match with simple rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Tackling is resolved by duel cards: Each player has the same set of cards ranging from 1-10. To resolve a tackling they simultaneously chose a card and the higher card wins, but if the difference is too high, a foul happens, making each tackling an exciting duel.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A set of advanced rules and tactic cards can be used to add even more details of a real football match.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
